  "text": "This partition of hereditary properties was first discovered by Scheinerman and Zito [CITATION_1] . As for the precise results, parts (i) and (ii) were established by Balogh, Bollobás and Weinreich [CITATION_2] , part (iii) was also established by Balogh, Bollobás and Weinreich [14, [CITATION_3] and part (iv) was established by Bollobás and Thomason [19] . Part (iv) has been well-studied, including the o(1) error term [CITATION_4] . It has also been generalized. Bollobás and Thomason [20] define c p (H ) as follows:",
